The paper discusses recent advances in Neural Architecture Search (NAS), which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed method involves using Transformer agents to transfer knowledge between multiple search spaces and tasks, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. Additionally, the paper mentions the importance of search space definition and algorithm complexity, which are topics commonly discussed in the neural evolution (cs.NE) subfield.
